1
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:05,880
What are you laughing at?

2
00:00:05,960 --> 00:00:07,680
Look at how the girls look,
what’s up? They look like new immigrants.

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:11,080
I can’t believe I let you
dress them in those pigtails.

4
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:12,520
No way, it looks really nice.

5
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:13,440
Right, girls? It’s pretty, isn’t it?

6
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:14,840
It hurts.
-It’s tight on me.

7
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:18,120
Okay, don’t touch or scratch,
it’s tight and the hairstyle will get ruined.

8
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:19,760
You’re ruining the kids.

9
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:21,920
What do you want? That’s Grandma Chava, you know her.

10
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,000
What’s wrong with you? Grandma Chava,
she’s just a sweet old lady.

11
00:00:25,080 --> 00:00:28,440
A tough, violent, and bitter woman.

12
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:30,680
Trust me, you don’t want to mess with her.

13
00:00:31,520 --> 00:00:33,680
In a second, you’ll tell me
she’s connected to crime families in the country.

14
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:36,320
I wouldn’t be surprised.
-That’s fine.

15
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,560
How long is she staying with your parents?

16
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:40,800
Until the renovations in her assisted living place are done.

17
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:42,320
Really.
-Sunday, I think.

18
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:46,360
Why are you looking at me? Look at the road.

19
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:48,400
You know I could look really good as an aunt.

20
00:00:48,720 --> 00:00:51,400
What an idiot.
-No, I’m serious. Should I pull over and do it for you?

21
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:52,680
Honey, if you don’t want

22
00:00:52,760 --> 00:00:57,960
me to turn into a tough, violent, and bitter woman,

23
00:00:58,520 --> 00:01:00,600
then you better chill out.
-What did I say?

24
00:01:06,320 --> 00:01:08,080
Look at me, look at me and...

25
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:23,000
Three, four and...
-Shabbat Shalom.

26
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:24,520
Don’t run.

27
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Walk nicely.

28
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:29,840
Mom? Dad?

29
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,520
What’s this? It’s freezing in here.

30
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:34,840
Grandma doesn’t like it when it’s hot.
-Okay, but it’s cold in here like a grave.

31
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:36,160
She’s not even here.

32
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:38,160
She likes to pop up unexpectedly,

33
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:40,120
she says it keeps them alert.

34
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,240
Come on, she’s 80,
how surprising can it be?

35
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:43,200
She’s not here?

36
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:45,240
Oh my God, Pinchas, you scared me, what happened to you?

37
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:46,600
Where did you come from?
-From the room. She’s not here?

38
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:47,520
No.

39
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,280
Alright, quick, Shabbat Shalom.

40
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:50,840
Okay, I’m going to see what’s happening in the kitchen.

41
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:53,800
Pinchas, Pinchas, can you
turn down the AC? I’m freezing.

42
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:57,240
Can’t do it. Chava says
it has to stay at 16 degrees in the place,

43
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:59,760
one degree higher is not civilized.
-What nonsense.

44
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:00,840
I know, sit down,

45
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:04,560
I know and you know that you shouldn’t touch a suspicious object,
not even get close.

46
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,680
No, you’re not normal.

47
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:08,120
I’ve been locked in my room for four days.
-Why?

48
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:10,120
Why? To reduce friction between me and her.

49
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:11,520
No, you’re not sane, huh?

50
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:12,840
And what happens if you need to go to the bathroom?

51
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,160
I have a bucket.

52
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:16,440
Okay, you didn’t see me, I wasn’t here.

53
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:17,960
-And, and...

54
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,480
Mom.

55
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:24,320
I thought it was Grandma.
-No, it’s me.

56
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:28,280
Where is she?
-In the living room, spreading negative energy.

57
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,520
Didn’t you see her when you came in?
-No, she’s not there.

58
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:34,120
So she’s probably in the bathroom,
releasing negative energy.

59
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:38,120
What’s this? What’s this? You really put in effort today, huh?

60
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:40,480
I made a soufflé fish cake in the oven.

61
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:45,040
Dinner's at exactly eight, a minute later
the soufflé falls and the fish dries out.

62
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,680
Got it? Eight o'clock.

63
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,680
What, no schnitzels?
-Of course there are.

64
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:58,320
Shayka, I've been working since yesterday,
I can barely stand.

65
00:02:58,880 --> 00:02:59,880
Then sit down, take a break.

66
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:03,880
I can't afford to, Shayka,
I need everything to be perfect.

67
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:06,320
Otherwise, Her Highness will have something to say.

68
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:08,280
Okay, I don't want to talk about it,

69
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,280
It's Friday today.

70
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:13,600
Are the girls dressed nicely?
-Like new immigrants.

71
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:15,240
Are the curls tight?

72
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:17,560
The girls are curly.
-Great.

73
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:21,560
Not that it’ll help against Grandma Chava, but still.

74
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:26,360
I feel bad for their soft hearts, they're young.

75
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:31,520
Mom, it’s pulling me.
-I know, my dear, I know,

76
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,640
Just a little more and I’ll let you go, okay? I promise.

77
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,320
Go play with your sister.

78
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,480
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

79
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:40,080
Shabbat Shalom.

80
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,840
What’s going on, where is everyone?
-Around.

81
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,680
And Grandma Chava?
-No idea.

82
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:47,280
Good, because I really need to pee.
-You just went.

83
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:50,200
We stopped on the way, that crazy guy did
it in the middle of the street, I thought I was gonna die.

84
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:52,640
Honey, it’s not healthy to hold it in.
-Okay, okay.

85
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:56,760
What, he’s stressed about Grandma Chava too?
-What, he made me wear a bra.

86
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:58,360
How's Shay?
-Shay, not normal.

87
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:00,280
No, forget it, this whole family is not normal,

88
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:01,440
Everyone's stressed about Grandma Chava,

89
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:03,400
Who would think, Gila Almagor.
-Yeah, right,

90
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:06,680
Seriously, what’s the stress? An exhausted 80-year-old woman, what’s the big deal?

91
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:09,200
Enough, Gila Almagor is 80?
-What?

92
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:13,160
Cinderella, that’s what I am, Cinderella.

93
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:18,160
I held the house for her,
she worked me to the bone.

94
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:21,120
And she always had something to say about everything.

95
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:23,160
Criticism, criticism, criticism.

96
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:25,480
Shay, ease up on the schnitzels a bit.

97
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:28,000
I only had two.
-You had five.

98
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:32,480
One thing I promised myself,
I won’t be a mom like her

99
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:35,520
and I succeeded, I’m not like her.

100
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:37,760
Right, I succeeded?
-What?

101
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:42,800
Of course I succeeded, I’m not a mom like her,
she’s a monster.

102
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:45,840
Me, what an awful woman.

103
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,640
Come on, I’ll give you an example.

104
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:52,400
I sat with Dad and her in the living room quietly
because she doesn’t like noise.

105
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:58,160
We sat in silence like mice so she wouldn’t
have any reason to complain about anything

106
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:01,400
and then I cleared my throat.

107
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:11,760
Did she notice?
-I didn’t say anything.

108
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:16,880
You made a sound.
-She cleared her throat, Chava, that’s all.

109
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:19,920
You cleared your throat.
-Maybe.

110
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,280
Why did you clear your throat?

111
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,960
I don’t know, just.
-Just?

112
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:29,480
People clear their throats sometimes, Chava.
-People don’t clear their throats for no reason.

113
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:34,640
You need therapy.
-No, I don’t need therapy.

114
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:37,960
She doesn’t need therapy, Chava.
-I understand.

115
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:42,720
So you probably cleared your throat because of the dust in the apartment.

116
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:48,320
What are you talking about? There’s no dust here.
-There’s no dust here, Chava.

117
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,920
The shelves are full of dust.

118
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:55,640
It wouldn’t hurt you to take a cloth and wipe once in a while.

119
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:58,760
My house is clean, Mom, there’s no dust here.

120
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:00,480
There’s clean and there’s clean.

121
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,440
And it's not crying.

122
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,000
Besides, it's hot in here.

123
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:08,560
The AC is set to 16 degrees, honey. It can't get any colder.

124
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:11,280
So your AC isn't good.

125
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:16,280
You know you're a creation of a creative creator,

126
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:20,480
that color isn't good for your hair.

127
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:24,920
You're doing this on purpose.
-Mom, enough.

128
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:31,080
This is my house, and if I feel like it, I
can clear my throat as much as I want, okay?

129
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:33,680
You have a problem.
-No, I don't have a problem,

130
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,320
you have a problem.

131
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:39,680
I'm heading to the kitchen.
-Run, run,

132
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:43,440
you always find a reason not to face the world.

133
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,400
Right, Pen...

134
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,480
Pinchas?

135
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:53,800
And she's been here since Wednesday, Shai,
I can't take it anymore.

136
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:55,920
But it's almost over, Mom, just a little longer.

137
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:00,760
Almost over? She's as healthy as a horse,
she'll bury us all here.

138
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:05,520
No, I meant she's going back
to assisted living on Sunday. Not dead.

139
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:10,320
So, what are your kids wearing?

140
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,560
What?

141
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:12,800
Horrible.
-Thanks.

142
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:13,720
And the pigtails? Shai.

143
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:14,680
Horrible.
-Thanks.

144
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:16,800
So where's Grandma, actually?

145
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:18,960
Dad.

146
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:21,120
Dad.

147
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:22,720
What's wrong, missing Grandma?

148
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,840
No, I don't want her to surprise me,
I want to be ready.

149
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,400
Why are you yelling?
-Mom.

150
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:28,080
You startled me.
-Yeah, but why are you yelling?

151
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,840
You know Grandma Chava doesn't like it when people yell.

152
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:33,240
What turned out in the end? That it's also because of my connection.
-Okay, okay.

153
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:34,880
But where is she?
-I don't know,

154
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:36,080
if she's not here, she's probably in the bathroom.

155
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:38,200
She's not, I just checked there.
-Are you sure?

156
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:42,720
Yeah, Dad, it would be very upsetting
to find out I peed on Grandma Chava.

157
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:43,680
Again?

158
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:45,160
Excuse me?
-I was three.

159
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:47,800
You were a week old.
-It slipped my mind, and I don't want to talk about it.

160
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:50,280
So where is she?
-She's probably in the kitchen, driving Mom crazy.

161
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:52,360
She's not! Mom's driving herself crazy.

162
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,720
Oh, good, I'm going to grab a schnitzel
because I'm starving.

163
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:57,160
Wait, so where is she really?
-Maybe she's on the balcony, thawing out.

164
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,960
Honey, go check.
-When?

165
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,160
Now.

166
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,400
I just sat down.

167
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:02,440
Wait, wait, hold on, hold on,

168
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:05,000
Honey, have you seen Grandma Chava by any chance?

169
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,080
How nice, thanks.

170
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,920
What did she say?
-I have no idea.

171
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:15,160
Well, she's not there.
-What do you mean "she's not there"? So where is she?

172
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,560
Pinchas, was she here?
-Of course she was here. Did she disappear?

173
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,360
She disappeared.
-Dad, relax.

174
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:22,040
I prayed to a strong creator
but I didn't believe it would really happen.

175
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:23,560
It's fine.
-No, I'm dying.

176
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,520
Okay, we need to go look for her.

177
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,600
She's probably around here somewhere, we need to go down and search.
-Of course.

178
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,200
Wait, wait, we have to tell Riki,

179
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:31,840
everything is timed with her
and dinner might get ruined.

180
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,159
R Nia.
Chavcha to the
building.

181
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,799
Shani, come on, let’s go down.
-Come on.

182
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,840
Wait, just a second.

183
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:39,240
Pinchas, you said we need to tell...
-I’m going to get a flashlight.

184
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:41,320
Wait, but why me?

185
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:44,880
No, I’m dying. No, I’m really dying.

186
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:48,760
In Petah Tikva, may their memory be blessed. Son...

187
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:51,160
Curtain?
-Curtain.

188
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:55,880
She didn’t want to buy me a dress,
so I took down the curtain and made myself a dress.

189
00:08:56,720 --> 00:09:00,200
Isn’t that Sara, the heroine of the BIL?
-I’m Sara, the heroine of the BIL,

190
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:04,960
I survived life with Grandma Chava,
I’m a hero.

191
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:09,200
She chased me around the house later because of the dress,

192
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,440
with a ladle in her hand.
-Ladle.

193
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:14,800
After that, she said that’s why
I have beautiful legs to this day.

194
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:20,000
Hey, Riki.
-Hey.

195
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,360
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

196
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:24,280
I wanted to say...
-Today we’re starting to eat at exactly eight.

197
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,560
Okay.
-Not a minute later.

198
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,480
Sounds good.

199
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:30,080
I’m saying this mainly to you
because you have a tendency to ramble.

200
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:34,200
Me? Okay, I just want to say something,

201
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:35,880
how do I put this?

202
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:37,400
Like this,

203
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,880
wait, from the beginning, what I’m trying to say...
-Just talk, go ahead.

204
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:43,920
You see? Your wife should go into politics.

205
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:48,200
Seriously, she can’t say
one sentence without going around in circles.

206
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:50,680
Okay, so what I...
-You’re also a bit of a teacher today, you know?

207
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:54,440
That dress doesn’t look good on you.
-Grandma Chava is a lady, okay?

208
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:56,920
She’s a lady. Is that clear?
That was clear enough. Right, honey?

209
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,520
Is that clear? She’s a lady.

210
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:02,920
Shabbat Shalom.

211
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:05,640
Shabbat Shalom?

212
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,840
Hello?
-Adamka, you made it.

213
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:11,080
Dad, what’s going on? Where is everyone?

214
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:13,520
What, are you alone?
-Yeah. I heard Grandma Chava is here,

215
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,480
there’s a limit to what I’m willing to put a girl through.

216
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,440
Grandma Chava is the limit.

217
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,080
Come on, where is she?
-A lady.

218
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:22,360
What lady?
-Lady, lady, let’s go down and look for her.

219
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:25,400
Wait, wait, I want to say hi to Mom.
-Are you normal?

220
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:28,160
First, let’s find Grandma Chava,
then you can say hi to Mom.

221
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:30,240
If we don’t find Grandma Chava
in 20 minutes,

222
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:32,160
the soufflé will dry out, the fish will fall.

223
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,560
Do you want to tell her that?

224
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:36,920
Does she know she’s a lady?
-I don’t know and I don’t want to know, let’s go.

225
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,640
I saw she’s going to ruin my meal.

226
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:48,920
She saw I’ve been working hard since yesterday
and it hurt her, you understand?

227
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,440
It hurt her.

228
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,720
Did you check the attic, maybe she’s there?
-She’s not home, honey.

229
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:57,040
Everyone went down to look. Should we go down too?
-Let’s go down.

230
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:03,560
We eat at exactly eight, with or without Grandma.

231
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:04,960
Grandma.

232
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:08,400
Grandma.
-Honey, why are you shouting "Grandma"?

233
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:10,440
There are probably a lot of grandmas living here, you’re stressing them out.

234
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:13,120
Okay, what do you want me to do?
-I don’t know. What, don’t you have a whistle or something?

235
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,200
Grandma Chava.

236
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:18,200
You know, the truth is, Grandma Chava and I,

237
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,840
we never really bothered each other.

238
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:24,600
Lately, I’ve felt
like she’s not talking to me at all.

239
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:26,680
Better this way, believe me.

240
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:28,240
The last time I saw her...

241
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:34,440
How are you, Grandma?
-It was good until I saw you.

242
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:37,680
What are you wearing? You look like a farmer.

243
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:42,000
Is that a bad thing?
-No, it's not a good thing.

244
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:47,720
You're my grandson, what will people say?
That Chava's grandson is a bum?

245
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:49,640
Wandering around in rags on the street.

246
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:51,880
This is what Shani bought him.

247
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:55,040
Shani, is that the woman?
-Yeah.

248
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:57,040
Oh, come on.
-What?

249
00:11:59,120 --> 00:12:01,000
Did your wife buy you that?

250
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,200
Fathers
Sons

251
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:04,280
I think so.

252
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:10,480
So tell her to stop, her taste in clothes
isn't exactly her strong suit.

253
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:12,520
Okay.

254
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:15,080
What’s this?
-I told you, she's a tough woman.

255
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:17,240
But why me?
-But she's my mom,

256
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:20,440
that's her way of showing she's okay
and saving me in the process.

257
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:24,280
Okay, but why are you putting this on me?
-She's my mom,

258
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:26,800
she has instincts, reflexes, a survival instinct.

259
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,800
Say thank you that I'm buying clothes,

260
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:31,840
because if it weren't for me, you'd still be wearing
your underwear from when you were 16.

261
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,040
Why are you making such a big deal out of this?

262
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:35,840
Go, go tell your mom, let her buy you clothes.

263
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:37,520
Seriously, great, now it's on me.

264
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:39,320
Grandma.

265
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,680
Grandma.
-Grandma Chava.

266
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,000
Grandma Chava.
-Adam,

267
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:42,920
Adam.
-What?

268
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,320
She's been with us since Wednesday, give me a moment of peace.

269
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:50,120
Tough, huh?
-Tough, tough.

270
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:54,240
You know, Dad, I have to say
I'm actually getting along with Grandma Chava.

271
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:56,520
Really?
-Yeah. I think she likes me.

272
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:58,440
Liked.

273
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,240
What do you mean?

274
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,960
Adam, listen, she had no choice,

275
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,920
she surprised us.

276
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:10,400
We were sitting quietly in the living room as usual and then...

277
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,160
So that means we're doing the order here.

278
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:18,800
We're not doing order anymore.
-Excuse me?

279
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:23,680
We're not doing order anymore because...
-Because we're not Jews anymore.

280
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:26,440
Pinchas.
-We are Jews,

281
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:30,920
Chava, but Adam, Adam is no longer Jewish.

282
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:36,000
Excuse me?
-He met a girl from the sector and he...

283
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:38,440
Converted, Mom.
-He's in the process now.

284
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:44,840
He asked us to respect
his customs! And celebrate the holiday with them.

285
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:49,960
But you can come with us to her village,
Mukharrar...

286
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:53,040
for Eid al-Fitr, if you want.

287
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,520
Over my dead body.

288
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,960
Are you guys normal?
-For real, it was instinct.

289
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:01,080
Muslim? Muslim?

290
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,840
You’re not normal, you’ve killed me. That’s it, I’m done.
-Adam.

291
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:05,240
She’s going to kill me.
-Adam.

292
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:07,280
She’ll chase me with a ladle! She’ll kill me.

293
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:10,720
There are really nice girls in the sector.
-Oh, come on, do me a favor.

294
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:13,600
You just threw your son into the territories.

295
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:16,640
Worse, into Grandma Chava's hands.

296
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:17,960
You don’t do things like that.

297
00:14:18,040 --> 00:14:19,480
Adam, you’re right.
-I know.

298
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:23,200
But believe me,
four days with her and I’ve lost my humanity.

299
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,760
Adam, Adam, listen.
-Leave me alone.

300
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,280
-I’m calling B'Tselem.
-Adam.

301
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:31,240
My head is about to explode, I need
to drink something. Is there a café around?

302
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:33,160
What café? It's Friday today,

303
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,760
This area is full of religious people, there's nothing around here.

304
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,440
What, there's no place to sit for a bit?

305
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,360
Don't you need to empty out?
-Always.

306
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,400
But if I need to, then I’ll just...

307
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:44,720
No, you can't. People are coming back from synagogue.
They shouldn't be exposed to that.

308
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,960
Wait, there's the...

309
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,920
Sergey’s café right by the gas station.

310
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,960
Is that a café?
-Kind of.

311
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:52,200
Do they have coffee there?
-Black.

312
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:53,480
No, I'm dying.

313
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:54,800
Alright, let's go.

314
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:56,320
Hey, Sergey, make me a coffee.

315
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:58,160
Is there anything to put in the coffee?

316
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,720
Alexei. Sergey is the owner.

317
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:03,160
There's vodka.
-That works.

318
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:05,240
What’s up, you guys?
-Just for coffee.

319
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:07,520
Sergey, add more sugar.

320
00:15:07,880 --> 00:15:09,920
Alexei.
-Alexei. Sorry.

321
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,040
Tell me, Pinchas,

322
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:13,240
how long are you going to use the excuse of Grandma Chava

323
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:17,080
as Shai's limited and clueless wife?
-Calm down, I just found out I converted to Islam.

324
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:20,880
There you are. No, I'm dying,
this is a convenience store with plastic chairs.

325
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:21,880
Sit down.
-Sergey's coffee.

326
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:23,640
Where's Itamar?
-Guess.

327
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:26,400
Shame on you.
-What happened to you?

328
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:27,920
This is really annoying.

329
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:30,280
Shai, can I go with you for the rest of the patrol?
-Of course.

330
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:31,520
I'm with Pinchas.
-And me?

331
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:32,880
14

332
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,520
My husband ran away because of that one over there.

333
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:38,000
How much longer
until the soufflé comes down and the fish dries out?

334
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,520
Five minutes.

335
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:41,960
I'm hungry.
-Me too.

336
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:43,760
Just five more minutes, girls.

337
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:51,840
I know, it’ll be over soon. Okay, sweetheart?

338
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:07,480
So what...

339
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:12,560
How's it going?
-Fine.

340
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:15,040
Life. What's up?

341
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:20,000
So-so. So-so plus.

342
00:16:22,520 --> 00:16:23,560
Nice.

343
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,200
Yeah.

344
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:31,080
How's work?

345
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:35,520
You know, the same thing.
-Yeah?

346
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:40,560
Nothing new, no...

347
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,120
No.

348
00:16:43,760 --> 00:16:45,560
How about you?
-No.

349
00:16:45,920 --> 00:16:48,240
No... not really.

350
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:52,040
What, Mom?
-Don't answer her.

351
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:56,360
Until I get a chance to talk to you like this.

352
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:59,120
She should call Dad. Look, she’s given up.

353
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,840
In short, she keeps nagging him,

354
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:05,520
and he’s like not even listening
to what she’s saying and she’s going on and on

355
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:08,160
and he doesn’t care what she has to say, you know?

356
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:12,240
She just won’t stop drilling
and he’s like totally not into her.

357
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:15,680
Disaster.
-So what’s new?

358
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,160
Nothing. How about you?

359
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:20,880
Just let’s stay healthy.
-Yeah, that’s the most important.

360
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:22,800
Riki?

361
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:26,480
Not answering? Let her call Itamar.
-What a scene.

362
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:29,120
About a month ago, Riki calls me...
Well, I turned her down,

363
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:31,880
After five minutes, you hear? Are you listening?

364
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,160
Our neighbor knocks on the door, Riki's on the line.

365
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:36,960
And what does she call me about?
She wants back... you hear?

366
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:38,920
She wants back those boxes
of the shlayklech.

367
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:45,760
There's no point in me trying to make small talk, right?
-No, there's not.

368
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:48,000
Maybe
come on

369
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:57,720
Let’s go back to Sergei’s café and that’s it.

370
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:06,120
Well, I’m really happy to have
Friday night dinner

371
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:11,200
with the people I love most in the world,
my grandkids,

372
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:15,640
who love their grandma and I love them

373
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:20,040
and they don’t always come to her with complaints.

374
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:23,120
The mashed potatoes are cold.
-The schnitzel is salty.

375
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:27,880
Oh, you too? Great.

376
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:31,960
Raz. Raz, stop playing.

377
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:38,160
Grandma, you look really pale, you know
that color doesn’t suit your hair.

378
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:43,680
Six, Sasha.
-Alex.

379
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:44,640
Wow, I’m dying.

380
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,160
So you guys came back here too?

381
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,960
Say, and Vada.

382
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:55,600
Victor.
-Alexei.

383
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:57,680
Can you give me more of that coffee?

384
00:18:57,760 --> 00:19:00,680
Where’s Itamar?
-He’s over there, he said it’s because he drank.

385
00:19:01,320 --> 00:19:04,080
There he is again.
-Come on, really.

386
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:10,240
Sorry to interrupt, guys.
-Don’t send us home.

387
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:15,280
No, no, no. Listen up. It was
about half an hour ago, 20 minutes.

388
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:30,440
Good evening to you.
-Good evening.

389
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,920
I guess there’s no menu here.

390
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:36,320
Not really.
-Too bad.

391
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:41,040
This place has potential.
-It’s not mine.

392
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:44,240
Are you an employee here?
-Working.

393
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:48,720
Is there something the lady wants?
-Thank you.

394
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:53,200
I assume there’s tea here.
-Of course.

395
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:55,760
Grandma Chaya.
-Grandma Chaya.

396
00:19:56,720 --> 00:20:01,520
Excuse me, can I hide in your kitchen for a sec?
-Sure, sure, come on in.

397
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:04,520
You’re a righteous among the nations, you know that.

398
00:20:05,360 --> 00:20:06,520
Righteous among the nations.

399
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:12,720
I think her husband stopped chasing me.

400
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:15,200
But then, after you left...

401
00:20:17,280 --> 00:20:19,880
They left, they’re worried about you.

402
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:24,680
Maybe you shouldn’t run away like that.
-You’re sweet, worried.

403
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:29,320
If I were you, I’d be worried about the health ministry.

404
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:37,200
Do you see what she did in the kitchen?
-I only work Fridays.

405
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:40,400
So how do you protect your rights?

406
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:44,280
What rights?
-Employee rights.

407
00:20:45,120 --> 00:20:49,040
Just wait until you’re my age,
you’ll understand what social security is.

408
00:20:49,240 --> 00:20:51,680
Listen, I’ll give you a phone number

409
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:55,520
of someone who works there, Sergei.
-Alexei.

410
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:58,520
That guy’s name is Sergei.

411
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:03,240
It started with social security
then went to why I’m not married,

412
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:07,080
what clothes I buy and why
I’m not doing something with my life.

413
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:10,480
So excuse me, I’m resigning.

414
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:13,280
Your grandma’s in the kitchen!

415
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,320
I knew that balloon looked familiar.

416
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:20,040
I’m not going back there.
-Okay.

417
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:25,440
It’s really just for the next few nights,

418
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:31,160
I hope I’m not bothering you.
-No, it’s totally fine, it’s really fine.

419
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:32,880
It’s still not working.

420
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:36,840
Grandma, that’s the coldest the AC gets here.

421
00:21:37,320 --> 00:21:42,120
When was the last time you filled up on gas?
-What, that's Sh...

422
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:46,720
Sunday the antenna "enter the monastery."
-I won't be here on Sunday.

423
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:52,360
Is this the music you play for your hearts?

424
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:55,360
Why don't you play them "The Sound of Music"?

425
00:21:58,240 --> 00:22:03,920
They, Mozart's Requiem,
it's really full of life.

426
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:08,880
I see you've caught Riki's bug.

427
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:21,600
Okay, but it's as cold as a prison, in a grave.

428
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:27,080
What? What?
-Sorry.

429
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:29,240
Where is everyone?
-Around.

430
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:38,000
Grandma Chaya is alive. Sorry.

431
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:45,960
Yeah, an 80-year-old girl,
no pulse, no blood pressure and...

432
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:47,320
What happened?

433
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:52,120
An 80-year-old girl.

434
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:55,680
It started to crash with the girl,
no pulse, no blood pressure.

435
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:59,560
I peed on Grandma Chaya.

436
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,480
Excuse me?
-I was three years old.

437
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,920
Pee.
-What, pee isn't good?

438
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:08,520
Cute three-year-old, pee.

